\textbf{t-SNE analysis.} After applying PCA for dimensionality reduction, we further perform t-SNE to examine the intrinsic structure of the feature space. As shown in Fig.~\ref{fig:tsne_visualization}, samples from several classes form relatively compact and well-separated clusters, indicating the presence of discriminative low-dimensional manifolds. Meanwhile, noticeable overlap and local interleaving occur among some classes, suggesting that their feature distributions are partially entangled and may require more expressive decision boundaries and robustness-oriented regularization to achieve reliable separation.
